Ordered delivery here twice. First time the order was lost and ended up getting the food 2 hours late. However, they were apologetic and sent a $25 gift card. We ordered the Burger, Chicken Fried Rice, and Chicken Katsudon. They were supposed to be re-making everything fresh, but tasted like it was sitting for a long time. Freshness aside, the flavors were also surprisingly bland. We ordered again a month or so later with the gift card and tried the Gen Tso Chicken Sandwich, Orange Chicken, and Garlic Basil Chicken. The General Tso sandwich was outstanding and why I am not rating 1 star. I would ordered that again. The other dishes were again very bland and lacked flavor that didn't get boring after a couple of bites. The delivery driver also didn't have a mask on and we have been very careful with non-masked interactions, so was disappointed to be greeted this way. I could imagine certain items would probably be much better fresh and not delivered, but the overall taste was just lacking for me.

What do you get when you combine mid-western flavors and asian ingredients? You get Bites, a new and exciting flavorful fusion that tastes great!  It would be easy to pass by the location, but, make sure that you don't.  The outside is deceiving, inside there are lots of seats in the dining area and the decor is colorful with a tropical flare.  Our waitress was kind enough to explain the menu to us and answered all of our questions with patience and great detail.  The menu is broken down by different sections, but the most important are the small bites, big bites (enough for 2 to share) and the handheld bites.  Other choices are the ramen/bao, sushi, last bites (dessert) and of course many different drinks.  We had one of the lunch specials, Singapore noodles (rice noodles, sliced onion, carrot, yellow curry stir-fry, and your choice of chinese bbq pork or tofu), Philly Maki (fresh salmon, cream cheese and avocado), Soft shell crab sliders, and Bun Roast Duck.  For dessert we had Cookie dough chopstix and Blueberry yuzu cheesecake.  We loved everything that we ate, my favorites were the Soft shell crab sliders, the Singapore noodles and the Blueberry yuzu cheesecake.  The lunch specials are a bargain and the portions are large.  They also include a spring roll and miso soup.  You can order a couple of small bites in order to sample different dishes, split a couple of the large bites, or get a handheld bite for yourself.  No matter what you choose, I recommend several visits here and you will be able to order something different each time you do.  We liked it so much that we are already planning on returning soon.

Cute and cozy venue with daily specials and a not too shabby happy hour deal 5-7pm ($5 wine, $4 sangria [$20 a pitcher], $2 Miller lites - BOGO half off small bites).  The beau and I came for a quick dinner before meeting friends nearby at 8pm on a Thursday.  Not crowded at all, which was both refreshing but also worrying - but helped make the atmosphere a bit more intimate and the service efficient.  We stuck to the happy hour tapas menu: Tuna Tostada, Jumbo Shrimp Shumai, General's Duck Leg, Basil Cream Mussels, Taro Fries, and Garlic Edamame.  Stand outs were the Duck Leg and Taro Fries.  Disappointments were the Garlic Edamame and Mussels - last of which we could not finish due to the awful uriney smell. The waitress was kind enough to take it off our check and confided a lot of customers had issue with the dish due to the fish sauce... but whether that's true or a coverup for using old / bad mussels, I'll never know. I have been here several times and my experience seems to get better every time. FOOD and SERVICE TOP NOTCH. My friend and I started with the Crab Rangoon(Made with spring roll paper -unique and beautifully folded and delicious) and Emerald Goyza(The standout here was the sauce- as sweet creme wasabi sauce) - our awesome bartender Pat expertly recommended we dip the crab rangoon into the Goyza sauce. These appetizers were the perfect pair. Then on to RAMEN(the reason for our visit). I got the standard Ramen with pork. It was everything you could want on a chilly evening. Perfect flavoring and beautifully presented. A standout is that they give much more generous portions of all the veggie and meat goodies! Some ramen places have tons of upcharges or they simply go heavy on the noodles. My friend got the Duck Ramen which is unique and delicious - the broth is made from duck fat and it includes a huge leg of duck in the bowl. We didn't plan on dessert... but the head chef Derrick was hanging out at the bar and we told him how much we loved the food and then he just gave us dessert! That was such a nice surprise! The Tres Leches cake was amazing and I'm not a fan of cake in general - see the pics! Come here- you won't be disappointed. Great for small groups or date night.
I used to super love Bites and I still like it a lot, but they no longer have sushi and this bums me out.
Amazing food and service is wonderful! I've been going there for the past 2 years and have enjoyed it every time.
They recently “updated” their menu. No more sushi. Most of the dishes are seafood based. Not as many small bites. I’m sad. :(

very cute place, with good food and great ambience. came here with mum and J for dinner. Mum had the wassup wasabi- a wasabi martini which was very delicious and most of their cocktails were 8$, which is cheap, i think. We tried some of the buns- i liked the avocado tempura but not the pork belly or the shrimp. Call outs to the crab cakes small plates and the korean sliders, but i thought the ribeye tacos were a bit of a miss- its just ribeye with lettuce. we also tried the duck noodles but i was really full by then and couldnt do them justice. for dessert we got the chocolate lava cake special with vanilla miso ice cream- this was really good. I didnt like the cookie dough chopsticks as much.  the wait staff is good, they seem a little busy but were attentive and helpful. since they were a table of 3 they pointed out which dishes had 2 pieces on them so you can order the third if you like. they also have some deals available, we got 15% off since we presented the menu to them and we also unlocked free garlic edamame when we checked in on yelp.
Great prices for delicious food!
No longer serves sushi. Website features a huge sushi menu. Called w a big sushi order after we selected from their seemingly delicious menu and had to hang up and start over elsewhere. Bye bye.
Food was pretty good and tasty. There is a wide range of sushi in the menu. However, it was expensive.
Yummy little gem! Love their sushi! Definitely worth coming on one of their special days where they offer 1/2 off on select food items.
(Translated by Google) Excellent food my favorite one hundred percent recommended  (Original) Excelente  comida mi favorita ciento por ciento recomendable
Everything was great. Here is a peek of their Tonkotsu Ramen

Loved the concept of an Asian Tapas restaurant! Completely met my hopes! Wonderful, unique drinks and foods. Our waitress was helpful making recommendations and everything was fantastic. Will definitely come back to try other items on the menu.
The service is wonderful, and the food isn't much different.  Phenomenal experience and food!
I met the ruddest waitress ever.

This place has great during the week, specials.  $5 cocktails.  The ginger margarita is DELISH. Half-off sushi and really tasty small bites to share.  Was a pleasant surprise this first time I went a few months ago.  And now I go back regularly.
The sushi was yummy!! The ramen was delicious!! The waitress was attentive knowledgeable of the menu.
Excellent Maki... Staff is friendly and accommodating. Recommend.
DELICIOUS! Their cocktail menu is also phenomenal
One of our favorite hidden gems in the city!  Amzing deals too
Great variety of options, freshly prepped.  Good happy hour specials.
Great food.  Happy hour promotions change from day to day.
Overall I like this place. For some reason it's a little hard to notice if you don't know where it's located.
This place is great! Awesome taste and beautiful plating make it more of an experience than a meal.
Nice happy hour with food and drinks and great ramen!
Not worth the price. Could definitely find better food elsewhere
BEST SUSHI EVER!!!! AND PEOPLE ARE SO NICE,WILL COME AGAIN!❤️😋
You have to try the Sweet Potato Maki
Very delicious food!!!
Never had a bad experience here - love the food, love the drinks. Half rolls of sushi are great! The ramen is fantastic. Love it!

We had food for delivery from this place (crab fried rice, jumbo shrimp, taro fries and Korean sliders) and everything was so good. I would definitely order again from this place! Totally recommended.
great services and decor. restaurant tables not packed together making the atmosphere more relaxed. food is crafted and tasty.
If you are low in budget and want to try something yummy and exotic, come to this place and try their tapas, you can also taste the amazing jello sake beer. Have a great time!
So good!!!

I had the best sushis and makis of my life. I have tried the "Bites makis" and they were soooo good. We also shared couples of things with my friends and everything was great. The restaurant is very cozy and decoration is nice. There is a fireplace but we didn't had the chance to eat close. I will come back again and I will recommend this place to my friends.
Service was great, food was great. No complaints.
My 2nd favorite restaurant under Gyu Kaku. Menu is full of choices.  Every single thing I've had was delicious.
Good

Great Bites...my favorite was Tuna Tostado.  Also tried 7 other bites ...split with my man...we were stuffed.  Samosa great...Red Curry Corn Fritters...loved the Bao ...Duck tasted a Lil fishy...I'm thinking fish sauce instead of hoisin...other than that...buy one get 1 half off small bites Monday.
Never disappoint
Fantastic food. Try the spicy wontons they make the meal.
Spicy sake and plum wine, need I say more.
The  food here is amazing and the drinks are to die for. I try to make it here once a month. The fish on the sushi is super fresh and they always have a daily deal!
Interesting find. Good food!

Our waitress, Jessica was the sweetest thing ever. She was very polite and patient with our many questions. The miso ramen was amazing! So were  the duck eggrolls, they had a good crippled to the wrap with a very subtle sweet undertone.
Love this delicious little spot. Be sure to check out $6 ramen bowls on Tuesday and the tuna tartare.
Love this place! Went in after pride, and the sushi is fantastic! The spicy crab Rangoon is die for, too!

Went to this place without any expectations. Left the restaurant very impressed. Food is cooked to perfection. We had the following dishes: - Clams with a slightly spicy sauce. Fantastic texture and amazing taste. Only thing portion was pretty small. Also doesn't bring enough bread to go with it. We asked some more bread and were charged 3 dollars for it - Pork chop with pomegranate sauce. O MG! Simply amazing! You can't afford not to try this dish!Wasabi noodles with rib-eye. Good. Special taste. Well prepared. Would prefer this dish a bit warmer temperature though. Waitress was also very nice though in the beginning a bit pushy for us to place our order Will come back again.
Best Nigirii I've ever had. Better than Okinawa. Very generous flavorful portions of sushi.
Revamped menu! Better choices and better value. We stopped going several months ago. We like the subtle yet significant changes. Try the duck egg rolls and shrimp shumai! We're going back.
Great food and atmosphere. My only complaint is that they always try to sell you more dishes than a normal person can eat. Order dishes slowly, starting with 2-3 for 2 ppl.

This place is amazing. Discovered it after wandering in for solace after Pride Parade. Absolutely adorable decor and atmosphere, relaxing patio/garden area. INCREDIBLE food. Highly recommend the Ocean Sundae or Lava roll. You will NOT be disappointed. My only qualm is that upon a few return visits, we waited for almost an hour for our sushi.
Really great food! Everything we ordered was delicious. My girlfriend said, "I think this is my new birthday place!"

The food was amazing and decently priced. I came here on a date we both enjoyed the food but thought the Sangrias fell a bit flat. They tasted like a watered down glass of wine and for the price they weren't worth it. After my visit I noticed others had similar comments about their sangria.  The service was great, one of our tapas had sat too long at our table before we had a chance to eat it and our server offered to replace it with a fresh one... Which I thought was really nice.  I'll definitely be back but I'll pass on the sangrias next time.
This is my best spot for atmosphere, with great food and excellent service.Give them gold star!
We needed to warm up and found seats by the fire- perfect!!  Just ordered drinks but we'll be back for dinner

The service was amazing. Our server was so sweet.  The food just wasn't that good and I would not go back.  The meat to bread ration on both the sliders and buns were definitely in favor of the bread and way too light on the meat.  The sushi was also just meh.  It was also supposed to be happy hour on the tapas, but we were charged full price.
The plates are beautiful and delicious. I would of had pictures but I decided to eat instead come see and eat for yourself...

Overall, I give them props for a really creative fusion concept. The sangria could have been more voluminous for the price. The pork belly dishes were really good. They gave us coupons for our next visit back, so I'll probably check them out again in the future.

Had a great time. The waiter was very attentive and helpful. Definitely give the ginger margarita a try and I had the spicy miso ramen which was very flavorful. The chile & mango sorbet was a perfect way to end the meal. I will def be back!

awesome Asian menu - a big must try is there pretty in pink ramen -- soooo delicious! They sure know how to spin their Asian style into something unexpected like their Asian Churros -- really good & different style of making it - they used those fluffy buns with a side of melted chocolate. I also had their Hot Geisha cocktail -- wow!!! It packed a PUNCH! really spicy and unique...I would love to go back there again!

This asian restaurant spot is unique and not a typical asian menu. They offer food flavorful from Thailand,  Korea,  and such.  The interior has a modern rustic decor and modern comfy seating including two cozy vintage single chairs by the fireplace.  Romantic. ;)  Started off with drinks that used asian flavors such as lemongrass. Small plates were mostly meat except for two and the main menu only had one vegetarian (no seafood) hence the four stars but tasty and a great experience.  We had the pink lotus noodles and mushrooms ramen noodle soup. Taro fries were crunchy with dip.  Lastly, dessert was very interesting and again used unique twist of international desserts with asian flare. We had asian churros (bao bun lightly fried with sweet spices) and best thing ever the coconut creme brulee (perfectly done crunch on exterior and smooth creamy inside with coconut and garnish with mint leaf in a cute ceramic cup.

I don't understand why there are no reviews for this restaurant at all!!! I love this place!! It just so happened that me and a friend came on a slow day, which was cool, it was like we were in our own private club. There was awesome service, delicious food, good music! What more can you ask for!
